title: Trump appoints Tulsi Gabbard as director of national intelligence
description: Donald Trump has chosen former Democratic Congresswoman Tulsi Gabbard for a surprising role as Director of National Intelligence. Trump praised Gabbard, now identifying as a Republican, for her two decades of service and broad support. Gabbard, who represented Hawaii's 2nd congressional district, left the Democratic Party in 2022, criticizing its stance on war and military intervention.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Trump nominates Senator Marco Rubio for US secretary of state
description: US President-elect Donald Trump has nominated Senator Marco Rubio for the position of United States Secretary of State. Trump praised Rubio as a "fearless warrior" and a staunch advocate for the nation. Born to Cuban immigrants, Rubio's political journey includes serving as a city commissioner, speaker of the Florida House of Representatives, and a three-term US Senator.
author: TOI World Desk

title: South African tiger farms illegally smuggling body parts, says charity
description: Biggest tiger farms outside Asia are operating freely in South Africa, Four Paws animal charity saysThe largest tiger farms outside Asia are operating freely in South Africa, facilitating the illegal smuggling of tiger body parts, according to a report by an animal welfare charity.Research by Four Paws, which is campaigning to shut down South Africa’s big cat industry, found 103 places in the country where tigers were kept in captivity in 2023 or 2024 or had been kept during the previous three years. title: Mystery surrounds John Smyth after leaving UK and Zimbabwe for South Africa
description: Smyth enjoyed ‘opulent lifestyle’ in Cape Town after he was barred from Zimbabwe, where he abused boys at summer campsThe evangelical Christian barrister John Smyth abused as many as 130 boys and young men in the UK, Zimbabwe and possibly other African countries but an independent review has said there remains little concrete information on his time in South Africa.The review into the Anglican church’s handling of Smyth’s abuses said he might have been brought to justice had Justin Welby, who on Tuesday announced he would step down as archbishop of Canterbury, formally reported him to the police when he found out in 2013.
